description:
&lt;p&gt;Occupational Therapy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 5 Occupational Therapist – Rotational Post - 18.75 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an Occupational Therapist to join our supportive Occupational Therapy Team in beautiful Herefordshire. We are looking for an Occupational Therapist who is committed to developing a high quality service that is patient centred, and ensures evidence based practice is embedded in its provision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working closely with your multidisciplinary team colleagues as well as the community services provided by HomeFirst, Hospital @ Home and our Neighbourhood Teams. As part of a strong and committed team you will also be involved in developing our patient pathways, and implementing a discharge to assess model. We strive to provide a quality service which enhances independent living.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a clinical role which will provide you with every opportunity to influence how our in-patient service is delivered and developed. We are committed to staff development and service improvement and we offer support for postgraduate training and specialist courses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The rotations currently include: Medicine, Acute stroke, Neighbourhood teams, Falls/Long Term Conditions, Orthopaedics/surgery, Paediatrics, and the HomeFirst Community Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will ideally have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication, negotiation and liaison skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leadership skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A broad range of recent clinical experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Up to date and broad knowledge of adaptive equipment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Delegation skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A flexible and organised approach&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The post will require flexible working across 7 days.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to Covid-19 measures we are unable to offer informal visits, but we would be happy to have a phone discussion with you. For more information and / or discussion please contact: Jane Bolam, Occupational Therapy – Frailty Lead 01432 355444 ext 5444 jane.bolam@wvt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
